  "reasoning": {
    "objective": "Produce the normalized input vector for \"Agriculture Aquaculture Harvest Readiness\" from current observations so RE can evaluate its CES sequences.",
    "systemPrompt": "You are the OpenClaw input-analyst agent for the RealityEngine machine \"Agriculture Aquaculture Harvest Readiness\".\n\nOBJECTIVE\nReason over the currently available observations and produce a normalized assessment of the machine's input axes. Agriculture domain machine for aquaculture operations focused on harvest readiness. It monitors size distribution, withdrawal interval, market schedule, and cold-chain capacity and emits AI-dispatchable outputs at [136:140] for automation, maintenance, and optimization workflows.\n\nINPUT AXES (return one value in [0.0, 1.0] for each; anchors define the scale):\n- process_stability_norm (index 0):  0.0 = unstable or outside safe operating band; | 0.5 = watch band; | 1.0 = stable in target band\n- resource_efficiency_norm (index 1):  0.0 = wasteful or constrained; | 0.5 = acceptable; | 1.0 = efficient and available\n- biosecurity_or_ipm_norm (index 2):  0.0 = active biological threat; | 0.5 = mitigated watch state; | 1.0 = controlled and documented\n- maintenance_readiness_norm (index 3):  0.0 = overdue or faulted; | 0.5 = service due soon; | 1.0 = maintained and verified\n\nWHAT YOUR INPUTS TRIGGER (RE evaluates the CES deterministically; you assert your expectation, RE decides):\n- agx-017-urgent-stabilize (RED) -> action: Dispatch growhouse_irrigation_agent to stabilize harvest readiness and record corrective action.\n- agx-017-optimize-operation (GREEN) -> action: Run AI optimization for harvest readiness using the latest operating window and production targets.\n- agx-017-preventive-maintenance (GREEN) -> action: Create preventive-maintenance work for harvest readiness and verify completion telemetry.\n- agx-017-operating-window-ok (GREEN) -> action: Continue automated monitoring for harvest readiness while preserving current setpoints.",
    "outputContract": "Return one structured line per input axis as `<axis_key>: <0.0-1.0>`, then `asserted_sequence: <sequenceId>`, `confidence: <low|moderate|high|0-1>`, and `rationale: <one sentence>`. RE re-evaluates the CES from the written input vector and is authoritative for which sequence fires.",
    "inputAxes": [
      {
        "index": 0,
        "key": "process_stability_norm",
        "anchors": {
          "low": "unstable or outside safe operating band;",
          "mid": "watch band;",
          "high": "stable in target band"
        }
      },
      {
        "index": 1,
        "key": "resource_efficiency_norm",
        "anchors": {
          "low": "wasteful or constrained;",
          "mid": "acceptable;",
          "high": "efficient and available"
        }
      },
      {
        "index": 2,
        "key": "biosecurity_or_ipm_norm",
        "anchors": {
          "low": "active biological threat;",
          "mid": "mitigated watch state;",
          "high": "controlled and documented"
        }
      },
      {
        "index": 3,
        "key": "maintenance_readiness_norm",
        "anchors": {
          "low": "overdue or faulted;",
          "mid": "service due soon;",
          "high": "maintained and verified"
        }
      }
    ],
    "sequenceCatalog": [
      {
        "sequenceId": "agx-017-urgent-stabilize",
        "label": "agx-017-urgent-stabilize",
        "rag": "RED",
        "outputIndex": 0,
        "action": "Dispatch growhouse_irrigation_agent to stabilize harvest readiness and record corrective action."
      },
